                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/986: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-02T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 2, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155. With reference to the telegram from the Legation in Honduras of November 30,
                    11 a.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me this morning that the terms
                    of the Honduranean note appear satisfactory to the Government of Guatemala and
                    it will therefore with pleasure attend the conference on January 15.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Honduras.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
